description: Sir Keir Starmer ordered the deployment of fast jets and refuelling aircraft from UK bases to bolster UK forces despite bloodcurdling warnings from Tehran not to meddle in the conflict.
title: Tehran threatens UK as Starmer scrambles RAF: Prime Minister sends jets to the Middle East as war rages between Iran and Israel  - and refuses to rule out further British action

description: Married Linda de Sousa Abreu, 31, was sentenced to 15 months for having sex with  serial burglar Linton Weirich in his prison cell at HMP Wandsworth last June.
title: Married prison guard who was filmed having sex with an inmate is FREED from jail after just five months

description: EXCLUSIVE: A A couple who defied a council enforcement order to remove a £10,000 set of gates have had to tear them down in a humiliating defeat.
title: A gate too far! Couple who lost bitter war against neighbours over Bond-villain mansion finally remove illegal barrier after failing in their attempt to create a new access route

description: The National Institute for Health and Care Excellence (NICE) has refused the 'miracle' drugs lecanemab and donanemab for use on the NHS as they are too expensive to justify.
title: NHS patients battling Alzheimer's WON'T be offered 'miracle' drugs as health watchdog rules they are 'too expensive to justify'

description: In a brazen display of criminality, a pair of masked car thieves are demonstrating to a TV film crew the ease and speed with which they can steal luxury cars.
title: Secrets of the keyless car thieves: As an epidemic sweeps Britain, real-life criminals show Channel 4 crew how quick - and easy - it is to steal a £24,000 SUV from a suburban drive just like yours in only 20 seconds

description: Although Trooping the Colour is meant to mark the official birthday of the reigning monarch, it was little Prince Louis who stole the show.
title: Moment cheeky Prince Louis leaves older brother George giggling during Trooping the Colour parade

description: The row has kicked off in the peaceful village of Stoke Poges in Buckinghamshire, where Doreen Beacom has lived for 25 years in her semi-detached house
title: Woman, 75, in £600k house furious after next-door neighbour demolishes home 'without permission' making her life a 'nightmare'

description: Many will be familiar with the old adage 'an Englishman's home is his castle' - but what happens when homeowners feel they are coming under attack?
title: Vigilante Brits: Homeowners who took the law into their own hands... and why some were jailed for it

description: A man who police say intentionally drove into a crowd of protestors at a 'No Kings Day' rally in Virginia has been arrested and charged. Joseph R. Checklick Jr., 21, drove his SUV through a crowd.
title: Man arrested after 'intentionally' driving into crowd of protesters at 'No Kings Day' rally in Virginia
